text.section:
As funds are available, Leslie County shall construct a memorial to those who perished, which shall include but not be limited to:
A monument to the miners, to be built at the mine site with the names of the thirty-eight (38) miners who lost their lives and the one (1) survivor;
Informational materials about the mining disaster;
Signage, off-street parking, and other features to encourage visitors; and
A plan for construction and periodic maintenance of the monument site.
